				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The helper functions are for basic things like adjusting a secondary stack pointer. Inlining them would apparently bloat code too much. It uses a lot of small helper routines. Conceptually it's no different than the compiler outputting the same code inline, just smaller. Look at the runtime source to see what they do.</div>

