				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The C runtime library is not optional when you want to use CC65. Almost all of its generated code depends on it.<br /><br />By the way, the linker is a &quot;lazy linker&quot;, meaning that any modules within the CRT library that you do not use (i.e. any individual .s/.o files from it with no references linking to them) do not get linked into your executable, so the size increase is only as much as you actually use from the CRT.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

