						<div class="postbody">Some compilers split the runtime library into separate parts, one with said &quot;very basic things&quot; needed by even &quot;freestanding&quot; C and one needed only by code that includes a header from the standard library. For example, GCC has libgcc and libc respectively for C and libsupc++ and libstdc++ for C++. Does cc65 have a similar split?</div>

